"id":"acc-AlternativeInputNeeded","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Add another input method"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Add a text input in addition to the pen control for an accessible experience."],"whyFix":"Some users can't use a pen and require another way to input information. Example: Typing in a signature.","level":"Low","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"accessibility"}},{"id":"acc-HelpfulControlSettingNeeded","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Missing helpful control settings"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Select the warning and set the item property to true to enable control setting."],"whyFix":"Changing this property setting will give the user better information about the function of the controls in your app.","level":"Medium","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"accessibility"}},{"id":"app-UnusedVariables","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Variável não usada"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Remover a variável não usada."],"whyFix":"Essa variável está declarada, mas não é referenciada por nenhum controle, portanto não é necessária.","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"performance","level":"Medium"}},{"id":"app-CollectingReadOnlyTable","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Collection is initialized but never updated"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Replace the Collect or ClearCollect with a named formula on App.Formulas. For example, MyTable = Filter(source, condition). Named formulas are computed when their inputs change and do not carry the tracking cost of a collection."],"whyFix":"Collections are meant to be updated. Power Apps does extra work to keep track of every collection so that anything depending on it stays in sync when the data changes. When the data never changes after it is set, that tracking work is wasted. A named formula gives the same data without the extra cost.","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"performance","level":"Medium"}},{"id":"app-CrossScreenEventDependencies","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Event rule references a control on another screen"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Move the work to an event on the owning screen (for example, Screen.OnVisible), or pass state between screens using Navigate's context parameter or a global variable and react to it on the target screen."],"whyFix":"Event rules (such as OnStart, OnVisible, and OnSelect) that reference controls on other screens force those screens to load and initialize early, even if the user never navigates to them. This can noticeably slow app start-up and navigation.","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"performance","level":"Medium"}},{"id":"app-ForAllWithMutation","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Mutating a collection or data source inside ForAll may trigger excessive rule re-evaluation"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Since ForAll returns a table, pass its result as input to the mutation function in a single batched call. For example, replace ForAll(source, Collect(c, { ... })) with Collect(c, ForAll(source, { ... })); the same pattern applies to Patch and Remove. A single batched mutation emits one change notification instead of one per iteration.","For trivial per-row updates or deletions against a data source, prefer the delegable UpdateIf or RemoveIf functions called once outside ForAll instead of iterating with ForAll."],"whyFix":"Using Collect, Patch, Remove, or another mutation function inside the body of ForAll mutates the target collection or data source once per iteration. Every control property that depends on that collection or data source re-evaluates on each mutation, which can turn a small loop into thousands of rule evaluations and, for connected data sources, a network request per row.","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"performance","level":"Medium"}}]}},"invocations":[{"executionSuccessful":true}],"columnKind":"utf16CodeUnits"}]}